\title{Criteria for finitely-generated modules}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-19}
\taxon{proposition}

\p{Let #{R} be a ring, let #{M} be a module. Then #{M} is [finitely-generated](ra-004A) if and only if there exists an #{n\in\NN} and a surjective #{R}-linear mapping
##{\varphi\colon R^{n}\to M.}
Furthermore, if #{\varphi} is an isomorphism, then #{M} is [free](ra-002X).}